Package arb

Class Complex

java.lang.Object
arb.Complex
All Implemented Interfaces:
NumberField, Serializable, AutoCloseable, Iterable<Complex>
public class Complex extends Object implements NumberField, Iterable<Complex>, Serializable
The complex numbers constitute an algebraically closed field, a commutative algebra over the reals, and a Euclidean vector space of dimension two.

    • dot

      public Complex dot(Complex y, Complex initial, int subtract, int xstep, int ystep, int len, int prec, Complex res)
      Computes the dot product of the vectors x and y, setting res to s+(-1)^subtract+sum(this[i]*y[i],i=0..len-1) The initial term s is optional and can be omitted by passing NULL (equivalently, s=0 ). The length len is allowed to be negative, which is equivalent to a length of zero. The parameters xstep or ystep specify a step length for traversing subsequences of the vectors x and y; either can be negative to step in the reverse direction starting from the initial pointer. Aliasing is allowed between res and s but not between res and the entries of x and y.
      Parameters:
      y - the other vector
      initial - initial value to be added to the vector, can be NULL which is equivalent to 0
      subtract - must be 0 or 1
      xstep - signed step length for traversing subsequences of this (x) vector
      ystep - signed step length for traversing subsequences of y vector
      len - negative numbers are interpreted as 0
      prec - precision
      res - variable which the result is to be stored in
      Returns:
      res
